Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new PAC-Bayesian bound and a way of constructing a hypothesis space for minimizing the bound. The paper also provides experimental results demonstrating the effectiveness of the proposed method. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses the Kullback-Leibler divergence to measure the complexity of the posterior distribution. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new method for tuning the trade-off between complexity and empirical performance of the posterior distribution. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper derives an alternating procedure for minimizing the bound. 
5. cs.ST (Statistics): The paper proposes a new statistical bound for PAC-Bayesian learning.
